import React, { useState } from 'react'; import './profile.css'; const Profile = () => { const [formData, setFormData] = useState({ firstName: 'Gururaj', lastName: 'Kamble', password: '********', email: 'gurruaj@gmail.com', phone: '1234567890', address: 'Ganadhish Park', nation: 'Sangli', gender: 'Male', language: 'Marathi', dob: { month: 'Janeury', day: '21', year: '2000' }, social: { twitter: 'twitter.com/gururaj', linkedIn: 'linkedin/gururaj', facebook: 'facebook.com/gururaj', google: 'gururaj.com' }, slogan: 'Project Complete Kara re Lavkar', paymentMethods: [ { type: 'Visa', last4: '1234', expires: '06/21' }, { type: 'MasterCard', last4: '8314', expires: '07/19' } ] }); const handleChange = (e) => { const { name, value } = e.target; setFormData({ ...formData, [name]: value }); }; return (
{formData.paymentMethods.map((method, index) => (
{method.type} .... {method.last4} Expires {method.expires}
))}
); }; export default Profile;
